Date: 23/1/1901
Source: Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page: 71
Edition:
Quote: The blossoms .. do not expand except during sunshine. In this they resemble such well-known flowers as the Star of Bethlehem .. and Pimpernel, which from its habit of closing its corolla as soon as the sun is overcast is sometimes known as the Poor Man's Weather Glass.
